### Why this will lift FITNESS (no fluff)

* **Tour length bias (core metric)**

  * Greedy-NN seeding + mutual-KNN reduces crossings and kicks 2-opt into better basins.
  * Early stop at (1.04\beta\sqrt{n}) ((\beta\approx0.712)) pushes toward ~**16.56** for (n=500) without spending cycles past “good enough”.

* **Runtime**

  * **No O(n²) sqrt** during candidate generation; only integer matrices are built when using int modes.
  * `expm1`/`exp` reduce transcendental overhead and improve stability of tiny updates (avoids stalling due to underflowed deltas).
  * Exact length computed in **O(n)** from coordinates, not `distance_double`.

* **Safety**

  * Keeps your `cities_number`, `input_path`, `output_path` intact.
  * Works for all distance types (double/int32/int64); double matrix only built when actually needed.

